title: Quiz 2 - Alphabetical Series
instruction: Direction: Study the following alphanumeric sequence carefully and answer the questions given below: C $ 4 B * © B 6 2 U 0 # K W & F 5 1 L @ 5 Y 9 Z 7 + 2 E 8 % N 9 1 ? Q 0 M > G STEP I – The numbers which are followed by a symbol are to be arranged in descending order at the right end of the series. (Just after G) STEP II – The vowels which are followed by a symbol will be arranged between ‘@’ and ‘5’ in reverse alphabetical order. STEP III – The symbols which are preceded by a consonant will be arranged such that 1st symbol (from the right) will be arranged at the left end, the 2nd symbol (from the right) will be arranged at the right end, 3rd symbol (from the right) will again be arranged at the left end and so on.   Note: STEP II is applied after STEP I and STEP III is applied after STEP II. And all operations will be applied.
